<h1>Pricing & Entitlements Explained: Self‑Service vs Full‑Service</h1>
<p><em>By Gwylym Owen — 16–22 min read</em></p>

<h2>Executive Summary</h2>
<p>AethergenPlatform offers transparent tiers that map to real‑world needs while avoiding cannibalisation. Compute ownership stays with customers; we price for rights, evidence, and support.</p>

<h2>Principles</h2>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Evidence‑first</strong>: every claim backed by signed metrics.</li>
  <li><strong>Rights‑based pricing</strong>: you pay for usage rights and support, not surprise compute.</li>
  <li><strong>Non‑cannibalising tiers</strong>: each tier has a clear reason to exist.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Tiers</h2>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Self‑Service</strong>: access to packaged assets, docs, and community support.</li>
  <li><strong>Assisted</strong>: guided setup, limited customization, priority support.</li>
  <li><strong>Full‑Service</strong>: private listings, custom adapters, SLAs, roadmap input.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Entitlements</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Asset rights (trial, evaluation, production).</li>
  <li>Support response windows (best‑effort → SLA).</li>
  <li>Customization (none → limited → bespoke).</li>
  <li>Update cadence (regular → priority → negotiated).</li>
</ul>

<h2>Compute Ownership</h2>
<p>Customers own compute for training/inference. We publish expected costs so budgeting is predictable; we focus pricing on rights and service, not hidden cycles.</p>

<h2>Evidence Alignment</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Operating points matched to business capacity.</li>
  <li>Stability and drift thresholds set per deployment.</li>
  <li>Evidence bundles attached to change‑control.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Anti‑Cannibalisation Design</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Each tier unlocks qualitatively different outcomes.</li>
  <li>Higher tiers include governance and risk reductions, not just features.</li>
  <li>Clear upgrade paths without discounting lower tiers’ value.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Billing Scenarios</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Dataset subscription (monthly/annual) with updates.</li>
  <li>Model subscription with support and evidence refresh.</li>
  <li>Project‑based full‑service engagements with milestones.</li>
</ul>

